sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT st_id) AS Number_of_Students 
FROM (
    SELECT st_id FROM student_feedback 
    INTERSECT 
    SELECT st_id FROM student_support
);

SELECT s.st_name
FROM students s
WHERE s.st_id IN (
    SELECT f.st_id
    FROM student_feedback f
)
AND s.st_id NOT IN (
    SELECT a.st_id
    FROM attendance a
);

external_knowledge:
- "learners excelling" refers to students scoring higher than the class average;
- "subjects they're being tutored for" means students receiving tutoring support;
- "beyond their peers' average" indicates scores higher than the average score for the subject in their class.

sql:
SELECT st_id, st_name
FROM students
WHERE parent_phone IS NOT NULL AND st_id NOT IN (
  SELECT st_id
  FROM user_accounts
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Beginner class' refers to class_id 0;
- 'Caretakers' and 'guardians' are synonymous;
- 'Kids' refers to students enrolled in the class.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT st_id) AS student_count
FROM performance
WHERE score > 90;

external_knowledge:
- 'scholars' refers to students;
- 'excel in Korean' indicates high performance in the subject 'Korean';
- 'average above the benchmark line' means an average score greater than 85.
